headline: Citigroup taps Adam Inzirillo from Cboe for equities business
summary: In his new role, Inzirillo will oversee Citi’s electronic execution platform, focusing on trading algorithms and direct market access offerings, the person said.  He will join in October as global head of the execution platform for the equities business and report to Sebastien Mailleux, global co-head of prime services, the person added.

headline: Greenland Resources Receives DTC Eligibility in the US
summary: TORONTO, September 19, 2025--Greenland Resources Inc. (Cboe CA:MOLY, FSE:M0LY) ("Greenland Resources" or the "Company") is pleased to announce that the stock began trading on the OTCQB Venture Market in the U.S. under the symbol GRLRF and that the Company's shares are now eligible for electronic clearing and settlement in the United States through the Depository Trust Company (DTC).
